earch muhtar kent born ahmet muhtar kent  age – new york city new york united states residence atlanta georgia united states nationality turkish and american education tarsus american college university of hull cass business school of city university london occupation chairman of the board the cocacola company parents necdet kent ahmet muhtar kent born  is a turkishamerican business executive he is the chairman and former ceo of the cocacola company he was appointed to the position of chief executive officer of the company in  and became chairman of the board in  in december  coca cola announced that kent would step down as ceo in may  to be replaced by president and coo james quincey kent continues as chairman of the board of directors contents  early life  professional career  –  –  –present  references  external links early lifeedit muhtar kent was born in  in new york city where his father necdet kent was the consulgeneral of turkey after completing high school at tarsus american college in mersin turkey in  muhtar kent went to the united kingdom to study at the university of hull subsequently he earned his mba degree at cass business school london professional careeredit kent at the world economic forum in davos  –edit muhtar kent found a job at the cocacola company in turkey through a newspaper ad in  he toured the country in trucks to sell cocacola and thereby learned its distribution marketing and logistics systems in  he was promoted to the general manager position of cocacola turkey and central asia and transferred the headquarters of the company from izmir to istanbul three years later he was appointed president of the company’s east central europe division responsible for  countries in a region from the alps to the himalayas living in vienna austria he served at this post until  promoted further muhtar kent became in  managing director of cocacola amatileurope in two years he increased the turnover of the company about  which covered bottling operations in  european countriescitation needed –edit in  kent left the cocacola company after  years of service returning to turkey muhtar kent became ceo of efes beverage group at anadolu group the largest local shareholder of the cocacola franchise in turkey and one of europes largest international beverage businesses he extended the companys territory from the adriatic to chinacitation needed –presentedit in may  kent rejoined cocacola after almost  years and was appointed president and chief operating officer of the company’s north asia eurasia and middle east group a position reporting directly to chairman and chief executive officer neville isdell muhtar kents rise continued and he was promoted in january  to the newly created position of president of international operations in this capacity he was responsible for all operations outside of north america and all group presidents outside of north america reported to him kents successful career took him finally to the summit of the cocacola company which named him chief executive officer effective july   he became chairman of the board and chief executive officer effective april   by  he is paid over us mm a year by cocacola muhtar kent is active in the global business community and currently is cochair of the consumer goods forum a fellow of the foreign policy association a member of the business roundtable a past chairman of the uschina business council and current chairman emeritus of the usasean business council he also was recently appointed as a member of the eminent persons group for asean by president obama and secretary of state clinton he serves on the boards of special olympics international ronald mcdonald house charities catalyst and emory university he received an honorary degree in doctor of laws from oglethorpe university in  he currently serves on the board of directors of the american turkish society and the national committee on united stateschina relations he is also an invitee of the bilderberg group and attended the greece  bilderberg conference at the astir palace resort in vouliagmeni greece on may   muhtar kent was awarded an honorary degree by the georgia institute of technology during the morning graduation ceremony at which he gave the commencement address in  he was inducted as a georgia trustee an honor given by the georgia historical society in conjunction with the governor of georgia to individuals whose accomplishments and community service reflect the ideals of the founding body of trustees which governed the georgia colony from  to  in  kent was listed as a possible running mate for hillary clinton during the  us presidential election  referencesedit  httpwwwhurriyetcomtrekonomiasp  httpwwwhaberlercomwallstreetjournalmuhtarkentkararinitelefonhaberi  leadership viewpoints the cocacola company   the cocacola company announces senior leadership succession plan   httpwwwhurriyetcomtregitimasp  alumni services cass business school retrieved    a b c muhtar kent chairman of the board and chief executive officer the cocacola company retrieved    httpwwwhurriyetcomtrekonomiasp  httpwwwperakendeorgekipmancocacolaninyeniceosumuhtarkentolduhhtml  httpwwwsozcucomtrekonomimuhtarkentinaylikkazancidudakucuklatiyor  leadership viewpoints the cocacola company retrieved    honorary degrees awarded by oglethorpe university oglethorpe university retrieved    board of directors  americanturkishsocietylocalhost americanturkishsocietyorg retrieved    board of directors  national committee on united states  china relations wwwncuscrorg retrieved    bilderberg  list of participants bilderbergmeetingsorg retrieved    ajc – muhtar kent honorary degree retrieved    time  hillary clinton wikileaks running mates  external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to muhtar kent turkish daily news december   newspaper radikal september   in turkish charlie rose interview with muhtar kent on june   adi ignatius interview with muhtar kent harvard business review october  appe