ases company statements leadership video library image library press contacts careers careers main contact us contact us main faqs by cokestyle water replenishment supplier diversity giving back diversity  inclusion our commitment to transparency our company overview about cocacola journey mission vision  values diversity  inclusion human and workplace rights our workplace the cocacola foundation leadership the cocacola system company history company reports sustainability report cocacola product facts us world of cocacola cocacola store overview operations leadership senior leadership vice presidents board of directors select an option chairman of the board muhtar kent share click to download a highres image muhtar kent is chairman of the board of directors of the cocacola company  from  he served as the company’s chairman and chief executive officer  previously he was president and chief executive officer and earlier president and chief operating officer mr kent joined the cocacola company in atlanta in  holding a variety of marketing and operations leadership positions over the course of his career in  he became general manager of cocacola turkey and central asia beginning in  he served as president of the companys east central europe division and senior vice president of cocacola international with responsibility for  countries in  mr kent was named managing director of cocacola amatileurope covering bottling operations in  countries in  he became president and ceo of the efes beverage group a diversified beverage company with cocacola and beer operations across southeast europe turkey and central asia mr kent returned to the cocacola company in  as president and chief operating officer of the companys north asia eurasia and middle east group an organization serving a broad and diverse region that included china japan and russia less than a year later he became president of cocacola international leading all of the companys operations outside north america  in  he was named president and chief operating officer and he became ceo in  mr kent holds a bachelor of science degree in economics from the university of hull in england and a master of science degree in administrative sciences from cass business school city university london  active in the global business community mr kent is a member of the board and past cochair of the consumer goods forum past chairman of the international business council of the world economic forum a board member and past chairman of the uschina business council a past board member of the national committee on uschina relations and past chairman emeritus of the us asean business council  he serves on the boards of m special olympics international catalyst cambridge china development trust and emory university  related items our company related posts board of directors muhtar kent building a resilient business in the eye of an economic storm jay moye davos  cocacola leaders join global conversation on growth resiliency our workplace the cocacola company recommends human  workplace rights how we achieve success is as important as the success itself the cocacola company recommends health  safety we are focused on the safety of our employees our visitors and the public sustainability report the fizz most read top  back  why sea glass collectors cherish coke bottles  is your name on a coke bottle  labelless cocacola cans tackle prejudice during ramadan  cocacola cake recipe  relationships matter why cokes muhtar kent never dines alone  the delicious dozen the  best cocacolas i ever tasted  cocacola ribs or chicken wings recipe  cocacola life arrives on shelves nationwide  share a coke  the hit campaign is back and it’s bigger and better than ever  the real story of new coke back most shared top  back  step inside new cocacola india offices  labelless cocacola cans tackle prejudice during ramadan  relationships matter why cokes muhtar kent never dines alone  run commuting takes off in cities around th